    <div class="container">
        <div class="grid">
            
            <div class="card">
                <h3>01 // COMPONENT API <span class="tag">UI</span></h3>
                <p>Full suite of interactive elements including sliders with interpolation, dropdowns with z-index handling, and focus-aware textboxes. All styled with the proprietary "Deep Void" theme.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3>02 // PERSISTENCE <span class="tag">DATA</span></h3>
                <p>Automatic JSON serialization. The framework detects state changes in toggles, inputs, and sliders, instantly writing to <code>SPAWN_CONFIG.json</code>. No manual saving required.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3>03 // EVENT BUS <span class="tag">CORE</span></h3>
                <p>A decoupled UIManager that handles input states. Features a "Don't Call Us, We'll Call You" observer pattern, reducing main loop overhead by 40%.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3>04 // ASSET PIPELINE <span class="tag">NET</span></h3>
                <p>Smart caching system for branding assets. Automatically fetches remote textures once, writes to disk, and uses local <code>getcustomasset</code> for future loads to prevent HTTP throttling.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3>05 // SECURE EXECUTION <span class="tag">SEC</span></h3>
                <p>Built-in environment checks. Detects execution context (CoreGui vs PlayerGui) and utilizes <code>run_secure_function</code> wrappers where available for maximum protection.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h3>06 // KEYBIND MANAGER <span class="tag">INPUT</span></h3>
                <p>Integrated InputService listeners for UI visibility toggling. Default bound to <code>RightControl</code>, fully remappable within the config structure.</p>
            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="terminal-section">
